{
  "text": "[20] The model we have used is a numerical model for diffusion in the forward mode, creating a concentration profile. We used the known CO 2 atmospheric history, to calibrate the diffusion model for our specific site (Site M). After we calibrated the diffusion model, an inverse method was used to obtain times series at the surface from the measured concentration profile. Here we describe the inverse method that is able to give an error estimate based on the 1s precision of the measured concentration profile. We describe the inverse method based on CFC-12 measurements (Figure 4 ). CFC-12 is only emitted by anthropogenic sources [CITATION_1] , its lifetime in the atmosphere is 105 years and the gas is chemically inert. Therefore CFC-12 is a very useful gas to test the inverse method. First we adopt an optimal function that best describes the concentration history of CFC-12.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "9442335"
